result.execSummary:
The defendant Ethan DJ Sonnentag was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.
Time Served Sentence with credit for 1 day of prior time served.
DNA sample to be provided and surcharge assessed.

records.addlTxt: Case Called @ 11:45 AM: Defendant Ethan DJ Sonnentag in court.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court questions Def as to status of counsel - Court is not aware of any private retainer as of today's date.  Per Def:  States he is not going to able to hire his own attorney.  Def wishes to speak with the State on his own as to resolution.  Off Record for Def to speak directly with ADA on resolution.  Case Not Recalled - P/S Scheduled - NOH given.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for August 31, 2015 at 01:30 pm.

3:15 pm case called. Defendant Ethan DJ Sonnentag in court.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Statement by DA Blader regarding matter. Defendant is requesting court appointed counsel as he is unable to retain an attorney on his own. Court questions defendant regarding employment, etc. Court does not find defendant is indigent and will not appoint counsel. Court will schedule a STC for defendant to return to court.  Status conference scheduled for July 27, 2015 at 11:45 am.

NOT PUT OF RECORD: Defendant Ethan DJ Sonnentag in court appears telephonically.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. DE states that he has not had an opportunity to speak with his attorney. DE is represented by Atty T. Johnson on a pending case in Waupaca Co. The court advises the defendant that he must make contact with Atty Johnson if he would like representation in this county.  Status conference scheduled for June 26, 2015 at 03:00 pm.
No operation of any motor vehicles without a valid driver's license.

Case called @ 1:12 p.m. Defendant Ethan DJ Sonnentag in court, in custody, appears via video with attorney Ben Szilagyi.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.  Advised of right of Counsel. Defendant will not be represented by SPD if released from custody. DA Blader requesting $500 Sig Bond. No objection by Atty Szilagyi. Court orders $500 Sig Bond.  NGP entered.   STC Scheduled - NOH Given.  Court enters Riverside Ruling in favor of the State and probable cause finding as to each count alleged within the complaint.  Status conference scheduled for June 9, 2015 at 09:35 am.
